<refnamediv>
  <refname>p:validate-with-relax-ng</refname>
  <refpurpose>The standard p:validate-with-relax-ng step</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection role="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>The <tag>p:validate-with-relax-ng</tag> step applies <biblioref linkend="iso19757-2"/> validation 
  to the <port>source</port> document.</para>
</refsection>

<refsection role="step-declaration">
<title>Step declaration</title>
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="../../../../xmlcalabash/src/main/resources/com/xmlcalabash/library.xpl" xpointer="xpath(/*/*[@type='p:validate-with-relax-ng'])"/>
</refsection>

<refsection role="errors"><title>Errors</title><para>
<error code="C0153">It is a <glossterm>dynamic error</glossterm> 
if the document supplied on <port>schema</port> port cannot be interpreted
 as an RELAX NG Grammar. </error>
<error code="C0155">It is a <glossterm>dynamic error</glossterm>
if the <option>assert-valid</option> option on <tag>p:validate-with-relax-ng</tag>
is <literal>true</literal>
and the input document is not valid.</error>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection role="implementation-features"><title>Implementation-defined and -dependent features</title>
<para>
<impl>Support for <biblioref linkend="relaxng-dtd-compat"/> is
<glossterm>implementation-defined</glossterm>.</impl>
</para>
</refsection>
